cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper discusses profiling techniques and their usage to improve the performance of software on a specific hardware platform. This topic falls under the category of computer systems and performance evaluation, which is covered by cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.PF (Performance), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also presents a generalized method for using profiling information to improve the performance of software from outside the corpus, which involves software engineering techniques covered by cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper applies the technique to the specific problem of selecting the most efficient last-level-cache, which falls under the category of programming languages and compilers covered by cs.PL (Programming Languages).
